<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="386" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[125,760,543,1012]" pageId="18" pageNumber="386">
<emphasis box="[155,248,543,567]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="386">Remarks</emphasis>
: This species is known from a single taxonomic entry. It was described based on 
<specimenCount box="[480,625,580,602]" pageId="18" pageNumber="386" type="generic">16 specimens</specimenCount>
from southern 
<collectingCountry box="[165,274,614,636]" name="Tajikistan" pageId="18" pageNumber="386">Tajikistan</collectingCountry>
. Later, it was reported from Kalmykia (
<bibRefCitation author="MINORANSKI, V. A. &amp; PONOMAREV, A. V." editor="A. S. Utochkin" journalOrPublisher="Perm: University of Perm" pageId="18" pageNumber="386" pagination="82 - 92" refId="ref12484" refString="MINORANSKI, V. A. &amp; PONOMAREV, A. V. 1984: Materials on the spi- der fauna of Kalmykia. In A. S. Utochkin (ed.), Fauna and ecology of arachnids. Perm: University of Perm: 82 - 92. [in Russian]" title="Materials on the spi- der fauna of Kalmykia" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Fauna and ecology of arachnids" year="1984">Minoranski &amp; Ponomarev 1984</bibRefCitation>
) and several localities in northwestern 
<collectingCountry box="[219,343,683,704]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="18" pageNumber="386">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="PITERKINA, T. V. &amp; MIKHAILOV, K. G." box="[357,679,683,705]" editor="A. A. Tishkov" journalOrPublisher="Moscow: KMK Scientific Press" pageId="18" pageNumber="386" pagination="62 - 88" refId="ref12571" refString="PITERKINA, T. V. &amp; MIKHAILOV, K. G. 2009: Annotated list of spiders (Aranei) of the Dzhanybek Research Station. In A. A. Tishkov (ed.), Animals of clayey semidesert in Transvolga region (fauna conspecta and ecological characteristics). Moscow: KMK Scientific Press: 62 - 88. [in Russian]" title="Annotated list of spiders (Aranei) of the Dzhanybek Research Station" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Animals of clayey semidesert in Transvolga region (fauna conspecta and ecological characteristics)" year="2009">Piterkina &amp; Mikhailov 2009</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="PONOMAREV, A. V. &amp; DVADNENKO, K. V." journalOrPublisher="Vestnik Juznogo Nautchogo Tsentra" pageId="18" pageNumber="386" pagination="47 - 56" part="9" refId="ref12639" refString="PONOMAREV, A. V. &amp; DVADNENKO, K. V. 2013: Notes on the fauna of spiders (Aranei) of the southeast of Russian plain and the Caucasus with the description of a new species of the genus Haplodrassus Chamberlin, 1922 (Gnaphosidae). Vestnik Juznogo Nautchogo Tsentra 9: 47 - 56." title="Notes on the fauna of spiders (Aranei) of the southeast of Russian plain and the Caucasus with the description of a new species of the genus Haplodrassus Chamberlin, 1922 (Gnaphosidae)" type="journal article" year="2013">Ponomarev &amp; Dvadnenko 2013</bibRefCitation>
). The original description and figures of the male palp and epigyne indicate that it is misplaced in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Lehtinen" authorityYear="1967" box="[228,315,783,807]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Agelena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="18" pageNumber="386" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[228,315,783,807]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="386">Agelena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and belongs to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lehtinen" authorityYear="1967" box="[484,574,784,807]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Benoitia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="18" pageNumber="386" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[484,574,784,807]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="386">Benoitia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(twisted conductor, epigynal fovea divided by septum). Therefore, we suggest a new combination. Because 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Andreeva" authorityYear="1976" box="[501,623,851,876]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Agelena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="18" pageNumber="386" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tadzhika">
<emphasis box="[501,623,851,876]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="386">B. tadzhika</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unknown between southern 
<collectingCountry box="[321,426,888,910]" name="Tajikistan" pageId="18" pageNumber="386">Tajikistan</collectingCountry>
and northwestern 
<collectingCountry box="[629,756,888,909]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="18" pageNumber="386">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
, and that specimens from distant populations have never been compared, it is quite possible that 
<collectingCountry box="[585,709,957,978]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="18" pageNumber="386">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
and Kalmykia specimens belong to separate species.
</paragraph>
